args: He disappeared under that wave!\nWe've got to do something, quickly!
Fear not. I'm coming to save you!
He's staying afloat, even with these raging\nwaves... He might actually manage this!
Little early to be celebratin' there, bro.\nWeather like this means business.
Ridin' when the sun's out and ridin' in the\ndark are two completely different beasts!

At night, you got no visibility, so you
can't see waves sneakin' up from behind.
Not to mention that conditions're perfect
for a riptide right about now.
Even for a total pro surfer, one screw-up\nout there could cost you everything.
Heh heh heh... HAAA HA HA!\nWhat kinda MORON puts himself in mortal\nfreakin' peril just to save one stinkin' cat?!
Sure, it's far from sensible to plunge\nyourself into the ragin' seas—let alone\nat night—just to save one little cat...
...but that just goes to show how strong\nthat guy is. If anyone can do this, it's him.
Rrrgh... Such ferocity. Nature's fury\nendeavors to swallow me whole.
But I am nature itself. These raging seas\nare but a part of me. I can do this...\nNay, I was BORN to do this!
I've made it! Now I will save you!
But a single misstep would have\nspelled our mutual doom. Phew.\n...You seem more chipper than I expected.
Yes, you can entrust the rest to me.\nAs always, I bid you to rest easy\nand enjoy the ride.
Whoa, thank you! You saved my cat's life!
You needn't thank me. I am nature itself.\nThe will of the heavens bid me to mount\na rescue, and I simply obliged.
And it is by that same will that I shall\npunish those ruffians with impunity.

F-forgive us! We won't come near you guys
again! We'll forget about the cat, too!
Heck, I'll forget about cats in general!
Whiskers? Paw pads? Never heard of 'em!
Hm. And yet the outcome would not differ\nif I simply dealt with you where you stand.\nNow, shall I pierce you through, or...?
D-don't kill us! We'll talk to our client,\ntoo! We'll say not to mess with anyone\n'round these parts EVER again!
That's not enough. No matter where it is—\nnot just here—I will suffer no one to rob\na single cat of their freedom. Ever.
Remember this: if you lot should ever\nagain meddle in the affairs of cats,\nyou will find NO MERCY!
Yessir! Whatever you say, sir!\nWe're SOOORRY!
Now, with fear instilled in their hearts,\nI expect we've seen the last of them\naround here.
Bro, I can't thank you enough.\nFor real.
Looks like our furry friends are happy too!
Say. You wanna borrow one of my cats?
Well, you've proved that you're trustworthy.
You said something about my cat being\njust like your Mineuchi, right? I figured\nmaybe he could stand in for him. Y'know?
Plus, the cats seem to trust you. \nI'll sleep easy knowing he's in good hands.\nWhaddaya say?

It is as you said before—cats are the
masters of their own lives. As such,
I would be betraying the natural order
by imposing my own desires upon one.
It is best for cats to decide how and where\nthey live out their days. This is true both\nfor your cats...and for my Mineuchi, too.
Heh. Looks like my pals are gettin' hungry.
Meaning they want me to catch some fish.

I can't disagree that the cats should be
able to decide where they wanna be.
But that doesn't mean they can only
do one thing at a time.

As for the cats who choose to spend their
time with me—I'm just one piece of the
puzzle that makes up their little kitty lives.
You feel me, bro?
And I think—no, I'm SURE it's\nthe same for your cat Mineuchi.
I...see. You've helped me to discover\nanother valuable perspective today.
Heh. Yes, yes, my frisky friends.\nYou shall dine as kings soon enough—\nthis I pledge upon my bow.
